cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper discusses a new probabilistic generative model for unsupervised and semi-supervised learning with natural images. It is inspired by Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) for supervised prediction in images, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new regularizer based on paths rendered in the generative model for training CNNs, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) or computational linguistics (cs.CL).
